                        <summary>
                            
                            <p>On the south wall of the central shrine in the Āmalakēśvara temple.</p>						
                            
                            <p>Rājarāja III. Year 31: 1246-47 A.D.</p>						
                            
                            <p>This damaged and incomplete inscription seems to record a grant of land to god Tirunellikkāvuḍaiyār by Arayaṉ Tillaiperumāṉ of Tiṭṭaichchēri and his brothers Ga[ṇḍarā dittadē]vaṉ and Uyyavandāṉ. It also mentions the land of a certain Tamiḻavēḷāṉ (see No. <ref target="DHARMA_INSSIIv17p0i0567">567</ref> above) as the western boundary of apparently the granted land.</p>
                            		
                        </summary>
                    </msContents>
